title: [Icemule Trace, East Road]
description: Tall brownstone rowhouses line both sides of the busy road, their round doors painted a wide variety of colors.  A gnarled birch hunches over the southern edge of the road, its roots snaking beneath the cobblestones and its bark lending the breeze a pleasant bite.  Beneath the tree, a scattering of bright green leaves litters the ground.  The bent stalwart marks the property line of a small snow-covered cottage standing back from the thoroughfare.

Short, sturdy buildings line both sides of the road here, providing homes to the merchants of Icemule Trace.  A gnarled and twisted tree guards the south edge of the road, its roots snaking along the dirt road underfoot.  Beneath the tree, a scattering of leaves litter the ground.
